</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="59" type="key">
<key pageId="36" pageNumber="59">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,690,951]" pageId="36" pageNumber="59">
<keyLead pageId="36" pageNumber="59">
<keyStep pageId="36" pageNumber="59">
1. Siphunculi 108–168 long, 0.04–0.07 times as long as body, with 0–9 finely pointed setae. Second segment of hind tarsus 0.92–1.36 times as long as base of last antennal segment. Processus terminalis 0.69–1.34 times as long as base of last antennal segment. Abdominal tergite VIII with 6–11, cauda with 7–22 setae. Pheromone plates on the hind tibia are located in the distal third of the tibia closer to its outer margin.................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pashtshenko, 1988)" authorityName="Stekolshchikov" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Pashtshenko" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[1034,1436,811,834]" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Neoceruraphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudosensoriata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1034,1235,811,833]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="59">N. pseudosensoriata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pashtshenko, N. F." box="[1247,1429,812,834]" pageId="36" pageNumber="59" pagination="1580 - 1583" refId="ref19549" refString="Pashtshenko, N. F. (1988) New genus and species of the aphid (Homoptera, Aphididae) from the Soviet Far East. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 67 (10), 1580 - 1583. [In Russian]" type="journal article" year="1988">Pashtshenko, 1988</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,690,951]" pageId="36" pageNumber="59">
<keyLead pageId="36" pageNumber="59">
<keyStep pageId="36" pageNumber="59">
2. Siphunculi 177–233 long, 0.07–0.09 times as long as body, without setae. Second segment of hind tarsus 1.24–1.78 times as long as base of last antennal segment. Processus terminalis 1.20–2.22 times as long as base of last antennal segment.Abdominal tergite VIII with 10–16, cauda with 5–8 setae. Pheromone plates on the hind tibia are mostly located in the middle part of the tibia closer to its inner margin................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gillette, 1909)" baseAuthorityName="Gillette" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[1140,1436,928,951]" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Neoceruraphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viburnicola">
