<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,583,997,1023]" pageId="36" pageNumber="59">Alatae viviparous female (emigrant)</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="59" type="key">
<key pageId="36" pageNumber="59">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,997,1199]" pageId="36" pageNumber="59">
<keyLead pageId="36" pageNumber="59">
<keyStep pageId="36" pageNumber="59">
1. Siphunculi 2.32–3.38 times as long as cauda and with 9–20 finely pointed setae. Third antennal segment with 35–69, base of last antennal segment with 10–20, cauda with 8–21 setae. Pheromone plates on the hind tibia are located in the distal third of the tibia closer to its outer margin........................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pashtshenko, 1988)" authorityName="Stekolshchikov" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Pashtshenko" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[1034,1436,1088,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Neoceruraphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudosensoriata">
